.TH "inherit_flags" 9 "inherit_flags" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
inherit_flags \- inherit flags of the parent inode.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" inherit_flags
.BI "(const struct inode *dir "  ","
.BI "umode_t mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dir" 12
parent inode
.IP "mode" 12
new inode mode flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a helper function for '\fBubifs_new_inode\fP' which inherits flag of the
parent directory inode \fIdir\fP. UBIFS inodes inherit the following flags:
o UBIFS_COMPR_FL, which is useful to switch compression on/of on
sub-directory basis;
o UBIFS_SYNC_FL - useful for the same reasons;
o UBIFS_DIRSYNC_FL - similar, but relevant only to directories.

This function returns the inherited flags.
